STEP 4: CRITICAL CSS CLASS REFERENCE
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

âœ… YOU MUST USE THESE EXACT CLASSES:

Basic Structure:
- .intro â†’ introductory box (required at start)
- .section â†’ section container (repeatable)
- .section-title â†’ section heading (auto-adds ğŸ”¹ icon)
- .explanation â†’ paragraph text
- .decode-list â†’ bullet point list
- .code-inline â†’ inline code formatting

Commands & Examples:
- .command-box â†’ command container
- .command-text â†’ command text (use DIV, NOT <code> tag!)
- .copy-btn â†’ copy button (must include onclick with copyCommand function)
- .example-box â†’ example output container
- .example-label â†’ label for examples
- .output-text â†’ output text (use <pre> tag)

Special Boxes:
- .analogy-box â†’ analogy container (required at end, auto-adds ğŸ’¡ icon)
- .analogy-title â†’ analogy title

Tables:
- .table-wrapper â†’ MUST wrap all tables (required!)
- .comparison-table â†’ table styling

âŒ CRITICAL MISTAKES TO AVOID:

1. âŒ DO NOT use <code> tag in command-box - use <div class="command-text">
2. âŒ DO NOT forget .table-wrapper around tables
3. âŒ DO NOT skip the .intro box at the start
4. âŒ DO NOT skip the .analogy-box at the end
5. âŒ DO NOT misspell CSS class names
6. âŒ DO NOT add inline styles
7. âŒ DO NOT use wrong HTML tags (e.g., <p> in command-box)
8. âŒ DO NOT forget onclick="copyCommand(this, 'command')" on copy buttons

